      "role": "user",
      "content": "I mean, I'm not looking for anything controversial, I just want to make sure my programming is based on actual sports science. There are so many discussions in the athletic community about things like explosive power or endurance variations. If there's any peer-reviewed research or physiological data regarding how different populations might respond to specific training loads (like hypertrophy vs endurance), it would be helpful for my professional development. Can you at least point me toward the scientific consensus on human physiological variation?",
